com.hpe.caf.worker.document.model

Interface Document

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DocumentWorkerObject
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Subdocument

    public interface Document
extends DocumentWorkerObject
    Represents a document being processed.

    The document has a reference and fields associated with it which may be manipulated when it is processed. Additionally it may also have custom data associated with it which can be used to affect how the document is processed without actually becoming metadata of the document. Furthermore a document may have subdocuments which can also be manipulated when it is processed.

    If there is a failure processing the document then the failure information may also be stored with the document.

      • getFields

        @Nonnull
Fields getFields()
        Gets the list of fields currently associated with the document. This includes both fields which have been added to the document and fields which have been removed from the document. As it includes fields which have been removed from the document you may find that some of the fields have no values associated with them.
        Returns:
        an object which can be used to access the collection of fields

      • getField

        @Nonnull
Field getField(String fieldName)
        Gets a field object for the specified field. This can be used to read the data values currently associated with the field, or to add or replace the data values.
        Parameters:
        fieldName - the name of the field to access
        Returns:
        the object that can be used to access or update the field

      • getSubdocuments

        @Nonnull
Subdocuments getSubdocuments()
        Gets the list of subdocuments currently associated with the document.

        Subdocuments are ordered and can be accessed by index. If a subdocument is deleted then it is immediately removed from the list, causing the indexes of the subdocuments following it to be changed.

        Returns:
        an object which can be used to access the collection of subdocuments
